race.comment: TWISTED QUEEN (5) was quickly back to form winning this grade against her own sex at Pakenham as favourite. She maps well and has more to give. She's promising and looks set to go back-to-back. EL TERCERO (3) brings three threatening efforts from the provincials in tougher company. He's likely to push forward and is well placed to be winning. SHYAMALAN (11) is a Hayes-trained stablemate to the top selection and can build on his debut win at Wodonga. He's won a Flemington jumpout since and has a future. LULU DARLING (9) resumes back plenty in grade and has a strong fresh record. Has jumped out well and may be the one to pop up at a price.
